cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it proposes a mechanism to speed up Reinforcement Learning. It could also be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with improving the learning process of an agent. Robotics (cs.RO) is another possible category as the experiments were conducted on a simulated biped crawling robot. Control Systems (cs.SY) could also be a relevant category as the paper deals with optimizing the learning process of a system. Finally, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) could be a possible category as the paper proposes a mechanism that propagates values through a state transitions graph, which is similar to how neural networks propagate values through layers.
